cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.DC

This paper is about proposing a standard specification for deep learning tasks, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper specifically focuses on deep learning and its applications. The second most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI. The third most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as DL is widely used in image and video analysis. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as DL is based on neural networks. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as DL tasks often require high-performance computing resources.
